The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Thursday, January 16, 2003 				 Mamata to tame teasers
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Trinamul Congress chairperson Mamata Banerjee announced on Wednesday that her party will launch a campaign against the spurt in incidents of eve-teasing. Banerjee said sergeant Bapi Sens death proved how insecure women in Calcutta are.																								Also on Wednesday, Soumen Mitra, deputy commissioner of police overseeing the probe into Bapis death, said he would request the surgeon who conducted Bapis post-mortem to clarify how many persons could have caused the injuries and whether the attackers had used any hard object or not. 																								According to Mitra, the investigative part of the case is almost complete and the sleuths will file the chargesheet within the stipulated time.
